    "macroSummary": "Consumer inflation expectations spiked to 3.42% in March from 3.00% in February, driven primarily by dramatic increases in gas price expectations (9.4% vs 4.1%) as Trump's Iran deadline creates geopolitical premium across energy markets. The combination of weakening durable goods data (Atlanta Fed GDP nowcast cut to 1.3%) with rising inflation expectations suggests stagflationary pressures are building, while Bitcoin holds near $68K ahead of the binary Iran catalyst.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market relief rally assessment remains intact but faces immediate binary risk from the Iran deadline, with oil approaching the $100 stagflation threshold that could trigger regime shift.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Prepare to aggressively roll up BMNR cash-secured puts if BTC breaks above $68K on Iran deadline resolution, targeting $70K+ strikes",
      "Monitor oil breach above $100 for stagflation regime shift that would favor Maturity sector overweight over growth proxies",
      "Scale short book exposure higher if 10Y yields approach 4.50% stress level amid rising inflation expectations"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Consumer gas price expectations spiked 130% month-over-month to 9.4%, signaling energy-driven inflation breakout risk.",
      "Atlanta Fed GDP nowcast cut to 1.3% from 1.6% on weak durable goods, confirming growth deceleration amid inflation pickup.",
      "Bitcoin 3:1 profit-to-loss ratio suggests local top formation ahead of Iran binary catalyst.",
      "Dollar strength before Iran deadline indicates flight-to-quality positioning ahead of potential geopolitical escalation."
    ]
